This paper presents a novel approach to deformable image registration, which is a common problem in computer vision and medical imaging. The paper focuses on optimizing the computation of the objective function derivatives, which is a key bottleneck in the registration process. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses parallelization and memory efficiency, which are topics that are relevant to the graphics (cs.GR), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.GR, cs.NA, and cs.MM.
